@karim79 what do you think about the following way: `Map map = new HashMap();
for (Map.Entry entry : map.entrySet()) {
    System.out.println("Key = " + entry.getKey() + ", Value = " + entry.getValue());
}`

this is ridiculous! so many different ways to do the same thing. let's make a new standard for user selects. we will call it `standard-user-select`. then we won't have these problems. although for backwards compatibility we should include the others as well. so now the code becomes `-webkit-touch-callout: none;
-webkit-user-select: none;
-khtml-user-select: none;
-moz-user-select: none;
-ms-user-select: none;
user-select: none; standard-user-select: none;`. ah, much better.
